          "textEn": "Another reason I find him so interesting is that he never talks just to impress people. He is thoughtful, curious, and surprisingly funny. He can move from a serious topic to a witty remark in a heartbeat, so conversations with him never feel flat. More importantly, he asks sharp questions. If I say I am busy, he might ask, “Busy doing what—living, or just rushing?” It sounds simple, but questions like that really make me stop and think. To be honest, speaking to him sometimes feels less like small talk and more like opening a door to a different way of thinking.",
          "textZh": "（我覺得他很有趣的另一個原因，是他從來不是為了讓人佩服才說話。他很有思想、很好奇，而且出乎意料地幽默。他可以在一瞬間由嚴肅話題轉到機智的玩笑，所以和他聊天從來不會覺得乏味。更重要的是，他很會問尖銳而有意思的問題。如果我說自己很忙，他可能就會問：「你是在忙著真正生活，還是在忙著瞎趕？」這句話聽起來很簡單，但這類問題真的會令我停下來思考。老實說，和他聊天有時不像一般寒暄，反而更像打開了一道通往另一種思考方式的門。）"
