          "textEn": "He was quite tall and thin, and he always looked neat and well-organised. He usually wore a plain shirt, dark trousers, and a pair of glasses that made him look serious at first sight. However, once he started teaching, he became much more lively than people expected. As I mentioned, he taught history, but he never treated it as a dry subject full of names and dates. Instead, he made it feel like a series of human stories.",
          "textZh": "(他身形頗高也偏瘦，而且總是看起來很整齊、很有條理。他通常穿著簡單的襯衫、深色長褲，再配上一副眼鏡，第一眼看上去會讓人覺得他很嚴肅。不過，一旦他開始上課，他就比大家想像中生動得多。正如我剛才提到，他教的是歷史，但他從不把歷史當成一門只有人名和年份的沉悶科目。相反地，他把它講得像一連串關於人的故事。)"
